						               													<description>Guspira is a funny, quick and suitable board game for all ages, inspired on the world of fire, devils, beasts and everything related to a &amp;lsquo;correfoc&amp;rsquo;, one of the most gorgeous and spectacular fests of the Catalan culture. Among the game cards there are some characteristic elements of this celebration as &amp;lsquo;Drac&amp;rsquo;, &amp;lsquo;V&amp;iacute;bria&amp;rsquo;, &amp;lsquo;Guita&amp;rsquo;, Devils or &amp;lsquo;Tabalers&amp;rsquo;, without forgetting &amp;lsquo;correfocaires&amp;rsquo;, brave people who jump and dance under the fire.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The main objective is to win the maximum number of &amp;lsquo;correfocaires&amp;rsquo; playing the pyrotechnic cards from the hand. But it is not always as easy as it seems to be, the dice has also its role&amp;hellip;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Besides the playful side, Guspira is expected to be a way of promotion for the Catalan culture. The cards show the most characteristic elements of this celebration and they have no text in order to be played anywhere in the world.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
